description:
5 Card Stud (1968): Western, Mystery, Intrigue, Maurice Jarre score,
Dean Martin, Roddy McDowell, Robert Mitchum.

Scene: a barbershop; Dean Martin&#039;s character is looking at the prices.

Sign: "Shave $1, Haircut $2, Shampoo $3, Miscellaneous $20"
Dean: "Miscellaneous...$20? ...What&#039;s &#039;miscellaneous&#039;?"
Lady: "Something you didn&#039;t ask for."
Dean: "Many people ask for it?"
Lady: (seductively) "It sells well."

-- Sly, smart writing like that fills "5 Card Stud"; and, backdropped
by Maurice Jarre&#039;s lilting soundtrack, it&#039;s a pleasure to listen to.
Like all good westerns, the actresses are also very easy on the eyes.
